org.dockbox.selene.core.impl.util.files.process

Interface SettingProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LowercaseListSettingProcessor, RemoveFirstSlashIfExistsSettingProcessor
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface SettingProcessor
    Setting Processors, when used in conjunction on a Setting annotated field within a ConfigSerializable class, allow for some lightweight processing of getting and setting the node value.

    Implementors must ensure that there is a parameterless constructor.

    While this is a FunctionalInterface for simpler matters, the two default methods can be overridden if required.
